    <stitle>EC-16 CONTROLLER - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After noting the relationship of the positioning marks made prior to disassembly, position
                and secure the EC-16 to the valve using the four capscrews. Tighten the capscrews to 50 to 80 in-lbs.
                (5.6 to 9 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mount the assembled EC-16 and antilock relay valve on the vehicle and orient it in the
                position marked before removal.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect all air lines to the assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect the electrical connector(s) to the EC-16.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Test the valve for operation and leakage prior to placing the vehicle in service.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Perform the
                <hotlnk document="s04032_HL0403208.xml" xrefid="hl0403208">INITIAL START-UP PROCEDURE</hotlnk>
                to assure proper system operation.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
